Section heading: Commencement

2.—(1) The following provisions of the Online Safety Act 2023 come into force on 17th January 2025—

(a) section 81 (duties about regulated provider pornographic content);

(b) section 100(6)(a)(vii) (power to require information);

(c) section 104(13)(a)(xvi) (reports by skilled persons);

(d) section 136(2)(b) (confirmation decisions: proactive technology);

(e) section 138(2)(c) and (d) (confirmation decisions: offences).

Jones of Whitchurch

Parliamentary Under Secretary of State

Department for Science, Innovation and Technology

10th December 2024

